    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tanks of various size designed for the development of photographic film. These often allow for the exchange of liquids without opening the tank completely and exposing the undeveloped film to light. Historically made of various metals, most recently stainless steel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
